# üöÄ MongoDB Installation Guide (Ubuntu 24.04 / Debian-based Systems)

> **Note:** All commands should be executed in a terminal (`bash`) on a Debian-based system (e.g., Ubuntu 24.04).

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Step-by-Step Installation

### 1. Import the MongoDB Public GPG Key
```bash
wget -qO- https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-8.0.asc | sudo tee /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/server-8.0.asc
```

### 2. Install GnuPG (if not already installed)
```bash
sudo apt-get install gnupg
```

### 3. (Optional) Re-import the MongoDB GPG Key
> *Redundant but included as per MongoDB‚Äôs official instructions.*
```bash
wget -qO- https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-8.0.asc | sudo tee /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/server-8.0.asc
```

### 4. Create the MongoDB APT Source List

```bash
echo "deb [ arch=amd64,arm64 ] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu jammy/mongodb-org/8.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-8.0.list
```

### 5. Update the Package Index
```bash
sudo apt-get update
```

### 6. Install MongoDB
```bash
sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
```

### 7. Start and Enable MongoDB
```bash
sudo systemctl start mongod
sudo systemctl enable mongod
```

### 8. Verify MongoDB is Running
```bash
sudo systemctl status mongod
```

---

## üì¶ Cluster Setup Script

### 9. Clone the Setup Script Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/FernandusJs/data4_mongo.git
```

### 10. Run the Setup Script
```bash
cd scripts
chmod +x setup_mongo_cluster.sh
sudo -s
./setup_mongo_cluster.sh
```

---

## üîç Post-Setup Operations

### 11. Access MongoDB Shell (Cluster Port)
```bash
cd /var/lib/mongodb/velo_mongo
mongosh --port 26050
```

### 12. Check Replica Set Status
```js
rs.status()
```

### 13. Import JSON Data
```bash
mongoimport --port 27017 --db velo --collection rides --file ../data.json --type json
```

### 14. Access Default MongoDB Shell
```bash
mongosh --port 27017
```
